; The daily value of TSI is determined as the arithmetic average of all adjusted LASP TIM observations
; made on a given day. A "scaled" TSI record is defined as a function of the reported TSI record as follows: 
; scaled_TSI = (1.d0 + scaling_factor)*reported_TSI where, for example, a negative 200 ppm scaling factor is equal to -200.0/1e6.
;

; of 5 part per million per year.
